a_1,a_2,...,a_n>0
n\in\mathbb N$$,  a_1+a_2+...+a_n=n
a_1a_2+a_2a_3+...+a_na_1\leq n
n=1
n=2
ab\leq(\frac {a+b} 2)^2=1\leq2
n=3
ab+bc+ca\leq(\frac {a+b} 2)^2+(\frac {b+c} 2)^2+(\frac {c+a} 2)^2=\frac 1 2(a+b+c)^2-\frac 1 2(ab+bc+ca)
\Rightarrow ab+bc+ca\leq3
n=4
ab+bc+cd+da=(a+c)(b+d)\leq(\frac{a+b+c+d} 2)^2=4
a_1=a_2=\frac{n}{2}-1
a_3=..=a_n=\frac{2}{n-2}.
n^2/4-n+1
n.
